4 Hours Ago He said, "I was at the Department of State Services (DSS) office when I learnt of the discovery of her corpse 47 days after she was abducted. "When her mother heard the news; she was heartbroken, she collapsed; we had to rush her to a hospital where she is currently being managed; she couldn't eat or sleep since then", he said. He described his daughter as a highly spirited girl, full of life and likeable by all who have met her. "I wonder why anyone would want to harm her", he added. "Hanifa was distinguished among her peers within the neighbourhood; she was a brilliant girl and loves her father so much. My last words with her the day she was abducted, she was about to go to a Qur'anic school when her mother asked to pray, she recited a prayer and I told her I've heard you, please you may proceed to school.



